Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: notipymail
Version: 1.0
Summary: A full featured email status notifier for python
Home-page: https://github.com/nbryans/notipymail
Author: Nathan Bryans
Author-email: io@nathanbryans.ca
License: MIT
Download-URL: https://github.com/nbryans/notipymail/tarball/0.1
Description:  A module for quickly sending email status and alerts from python
        programs
        
        This script was created to notify me when a job was completed (and
        sometimes include an exit status and relevant results)
        
        Notipy is compatible with both python2 and python3
        
        Instructions
        ============
        
        Get Notipy
        ~~~~~~~~~~
        
        From PyPi
        
        ::
        
            pip install notipymail
        
        From Source
        
        ::
        
            git clone https://github.com/nbryans/notipymail.git
            python setup.py sdist
            # Move dist\*.zip to desired location. Extract zip
            cd Notipy-X.X
            python setup.py install
        
        On First Run
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        In a ``python`` session
        
        .. code:: python
        
            import notipymail.notipy as notipy
            notipy.updateSendDetails('yourEmail@emailProvider.com', 'yourPassword', 'smtp.emailProvider.com', '587')
        
        This will create file ``senddetails.dat`` containing the following
        contents:
        
        ::
        
            email:email@emailProvider.com
            password:yourPassword
            server:smtp.emailProvider.com
            port:587
        
        Optionally, you can create this file manually.
        
        Sending Emails with Notipy:
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            import notipymail.notipy as notipy
            notipy.sendMail("to@address.com", "This is a message")
        
        Notes
        =====
        
        Use ``notipy.sendMailAsync(..)`` to send mail in the background
        asynchronously.
        
        Send status are logged in ``notipy.log``. The log file can be changed in
        the ``#Constants`` section of ``notipy.py``
        
        To query the log through python, use ``notipy.queryLog(5)`` where ``5``
        specifies the number of log entries (most recent to least) to retrieve.
        This operation may be slow for large logs.
        
        In ``sendMail`` and ``sendMailAsync``, there is an optional third
        parameter where you can specify a subject. *i.e.*
        ``notipy.sendMail("to@address.com", "This is the message", "Custom Subject")``.
        The default subject is "Notipy Automail"
        
